<br>
ok everyones epic has been obsolete for two expansions before this...<br>
<br>
though thats not a flame there is some interesting thoughts that come out of this.<br>
<br>
im a rogue. we have a curse and a blessing from a casual gamers point of view  though i only fit the casual mode cause i SUXORS.  anyway back to the point.  Rogues get their epic early.  Way early.  and some classes can get their epic early if they are backed by some power and freetime.  but a rogue can get their epic early without to much of either.   a nice casual hot guild can bang out a rogue epic without to much fuss.   <br>
<br>
but then you get where i am/was/who knows.   the same guild that can bang out a rogue epic very early ina  rogues life cannot usually upgrade the epic.   To some this doesnt seem like an issue.  Cept its like a small drip.  A drop over and over.    <br>
<br>
I explained it this way.  I said use the same equipment to fulfill your primary function for 7 months then get back to me. All the while averaging 30 hours a week of play time.  usually more.  then get back to me and tell me if it doesnt feel like your doing something wrong.   <br>
<br>
Like i said an easy rogue epic is both a blessing and a curse.  its a blessing because basically its a fixture of rogues pre60 power.  if it werent common as dirt rogues pre60 wouldnt be popular to group with in the generic way they are now.  its a curse because if your guild gets it for ya at the earliest possible moment they can then you might as well get used to no upgrades.  for most rogues that is.<br>
<br>
At first i thought monks and rogues shared this curse equally. then i realized that monks usually just used the haste on their epic. Then i realized mages had it much worse on a similiar level.<br>
<br>
notice that some mages have probably been using the same pet since kunark basically.  nevermind they might have been playing 40 hours a week.  its irrelevant.  because while the rogue epic is hard to upgrade for some guilds the mage epic was *impossible* to upgrade.  so many mages could get back to me bout that &quot;use a piece of equipment for 7 months to perform your primary role 30 hours a week&quot; And some could trump that and say try a year and half of the same &quot;weapon&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
So  *sad* for the mages.<br>
<br>
My only hope thought bout this pet thing is they honor the work that some people put into this game.  That they dont hand it out to everyone from a vendor or easy quest. vendor as they initially did for the cleric weapon.  easy drop for the 58 upgrade.   <br>
<br>
Such easy upgrades to something thats a mainstay or will be a mainstay to the class dont honor the game itself. So heres to uber hard mage spell drops.  though sometimes i dont feel that way.  specially when i want to fooking put my 7 month old mainhand to offhand =)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
