<br>
I don't really mind too much about some epics becoming obsolete, it is bound to happen especially with melee but on casters it seems somehow different.  Most mages get their epic at level 57 or 58 at the very minimum, few rarely get it before that.   However, the epic now becomes virtually useless after level 61 which gives you 3 or so levels to enjoy it.  Few mages will now have the incentive to try for their epics unless, of course, epic 2.0 is instituted.  Meanwhile, classes like druids and shamans always have that right click dot and in the case of druids dot + snare.  It is hard to make epics like that become obsolete because it is manaless way to cause dmg.   Melee will always be given better weapons and their epics are a nice stepping stone to get those better weapons.  I will still summon the orb for the stats, it just seems odd having an orb with a charge on it that I might never use again.<br>
<br>
